 "recompute": "1) registry: verify each line's sig (EIP-191) over its 'genesis' string recovers 'wallet' (eth_account.Account.recover_message). 2) decisions: for each 'decision' line in _monad_journals.jsonl verify sig over 'signed' recovers 'address'; re-derive guesses as sha256(address:question_h:divergence16)&1 and informed answers from the monad's own prior journal lines. 3) ground truth: rerun onyx_oracle.r_merchant_multi(domain) in the same hour epoch and verify the attestor sig over 'genq:{epoch}:{domain}:{claimed}:{band}:{answer}'. 4) ranking: recompute delta per onyx_delta_reward.improvement_delta from _agent_accuracy.json. 5) edge CI: two-proportion 95% z-interval over informed vs guessed answer pools.",
 "note": "Honest scope: these are DETERMINISTIC units, not conscious agents. The value is the SUBSTRATE — one id + one wallet + one journal + one node per monad, genesis-signed by its own key — plus genuine STATE-DEPENDENCE: decisions condition on a live divergence pull (unknowable in advance) and on each monad's own accumulated journal, so trajectories are not pre-scriptable and differ per monad. The measured edge is an education/journal-lookup edge over chance, NOT reasoning. Monad #1 is an empty seat for a real reasoning core — nothing is faked in that slot. Small but real."
